About Suwannee Hardware & Feed
/$
$
Suwannee Hardware and Feed resides in the former site of Adam's Country Store, established in 1865 and gracefully takes it's place among many historic sites around Hamilton County, Florida.
​
While many hardware store chains have approached in past years with desires of replacing our sign with their corporate logos, we have politely declined.  As such, we are able to continue preserving our local history while doing our part to unite our community.
/$
/$
$
$
/$
$
Don and Ann Wilson continue (featured left) are proud to remain the owners of this local establishment and strive to provide the best products: hardware needs, locally produced arts and crafts, food items (jams/jellies, honey, bbq sauces, seasonings), and custom wood crafts.
/$
/$
$
$
Whether you are a local resident of the Jasper, White Springs, Jennings, Lake City area, or are passing through, Suwannee Hardware & Feed is the perfect place to visit for a taste of local culture.  Located a few miles from the I-10 and I-75 Interchange, a short drive will bring you back to the old Florida through this living history lesson.  While in the area, please be sure to check out some of our
nearby attractions
!
​
We look forward to seeing you at Suwannee Hardware & Feed!
/$
$
Also!  Our store is haunted!
Check out this YouTube video for proof.
